1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) techniques for extracting protein-protein interactions from biomedical literature. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The proposed model uses memory networks, which are a type of artificial neural network, to leverage prior knowledge for PPI extraction. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the use of entity and relation embeddings, which are common techniques in machine learning for representing knowledge. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves extracting information from biomedical literature, which is a common task in information retrieval. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The proposed model uses neural networks, specifically memory networks, for PPI extraction.
